          "date": "2019-05-16 02:23:03.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-9667 lnet: Create new structure for sysfs peer kobjects",
        "message": "LU-9667 lnet: Create new structure for sysfs peer kobjects\n\nThis patch creates a new structure lnet_sysfs_peer for the\npeer_ni kobjects. This is needed so that the cleanup of\nkobjects and the peer_ni structure can be done separately.\nThe peer_ni structure is deleted within the spinlock\nlnet_net_lock but kobjects cannot be cleared within this lock\nbecause in the kobject_put() api, mustex is used which when done\ninside a spin_lock gives error.\n\nTo avoid this locking issue, peer_ni kobjects are added to a\nsysfs_peer_zombie list which is then traversed and cleanedup\noutside the lnet_net_lock.\n\nChange-Id: If7b868504aa8d0c9ceaa1fd0361be06986b8abfb\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Sonia Sharma <sharmaso@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/lnet-sysfs"
    }
  },
